HEADWORD: Telemotor
<hw>Tel`e*mo"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>th^le</grk> far + <ets>motor</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A hydraulic device by which the movement of the wheel on the bridge
operates the steering gear at the stern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

